Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.88,0:00:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we're going to discuss what is real success.\NReal?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.98,0:00:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Real.\NSo, that's the topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.08,0:00:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what would you say, when I think of that, what is real success,\Nimmediately people think that money and position and personal goals are what they consider is real success.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.78,0:00:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When I ask you as a spiritual teacher what real success is, how would you interpret that?\NI would, as a spiritual teacher, say it has to do with fulfilling your obligations to experience the presence of God to the fullest possible extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.52,0:01:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And to begin to realize that as you do this, everything reveals itself.\NAs divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.22,0:01:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As you ask me the question, the divinity of this moment is now revealing itself to me.\NIt seems at first like an artificially posed thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.09,0:01:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you realize that there is no such thing as an artificially posed thought.\NThat thought is originating from the presence of God as the reality of you and I sitting here on this couch speaking at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.81,0:01:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the presence of God as existence.\NFrom moment to moment, the existence of that which is real is nothing but the realization that God is the essence of all reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.92,0:01:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Lord. Amen.\NGod told me to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.58,0:02:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, a lot of people think that they're successful if they have money.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.62,0:02:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of them, you know.\NSo you've always said that if a person, as far as it goes, is if they do the best they can at what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.92,0:02:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.\NThat success will automatically come to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.46,0:02:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I don't want to put down material success.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.17,0:02:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be a millionaire and to be world famous and on television every day and have worshipful crowds.\NI don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.47,0:02:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to make that.\NThat's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.67,0:02:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how success comes to that person.\NWe need famous people to hang out around and enjoy their presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.92,0:03:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we get to share in the joy of their success.\NSo if people are joyfully successful, I say thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.97,0:03:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your success because we're all enjoying your enjoyment of it.\NAnd we all need Bob.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.01,0:03:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Bob Hope and Bing Crosby.\NThat sort of dates me, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.80,0:03:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would be a current example?\NWell, a lot of people, you know, they...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.82,0:03:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you give me a current example?\NWell, like, you know, fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.40,0:03:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they want to be famous and recognized.\NLike I were.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.14,0:03:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any people like that today?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.64,0:03:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People.\NWho is these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.92,0:03:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you name me one successful person?\NWell, many come to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.60,0:03:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean...\NLike?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Jay Letterman.\NWho?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.78,0:03:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Jay Letterman.\NJay Leno.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.54,0:03:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh.\NI see what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.14,0:04:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who they are, but it sounds good to me.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.12,0:04:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, politicians are, you know, famous.\NPresident.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.88,0:04:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWho is the president of the United States?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.10,0:04:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Obama.\NOh, Michelle Obama?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.62,0:04:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NBarack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack?\NBarack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.92,0:04:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack Obama.\NThat's a funny name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.05,0:04:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that his real first name?\NBarack?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.01,0:04:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NBarack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.45,0:04:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh, he seemed like a nice fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked him.\NAnd with the name of Barack, if Obama would become president, you really got to have something
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.48,0:04:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,on the ball.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.28,0:04:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was John Obama.\NSo, Phil.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.90,0:04:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my question is, real success, is it what you are in the world?\NOr is it how the world sees you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.21,0:05:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the real success is its own self-fulfillment.\NReal success is achieving the fulfillment and expression of your own potentialities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.12,0:05:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The world may or may not recognize that.\NSo, the world's response to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.04,0:05:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, real success would really include not only fulfillment of your own potentiality,\Nbut the response of the world to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's perfectly all right to be president of the United States.\NI think it's great that he fulfilled his potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.79,0:05:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also enjoy the fact that the world recognizes it.\NThat is a name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.28,0:05:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it?\NPhilip Obama?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.64,0:05:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NBarack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.72,0:05:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack Obama?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.34,0:05:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's his first name?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.54,0:05:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack?\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.60,0:05:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnyway, I enjoy him when I see him speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.05,0:06:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he's very eloquent.\NVery eloquent speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.94,0:06:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NMore eloquent than I am, he's very eloquent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NI'm glad he's president because he's very eloquent and sort of elegant, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.22,0:06:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Very elegant, yeah.\NOkay, but who you are in the world versus what you are in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.48,0:06:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how would you describe that?\NWell, who is the personality?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.27,0:06:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And what?\NIt has to do with function.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a what when you sit here and talk to the camera.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.12,0:06:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, I'm being a what.\NBut there is a who being that what.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NSo, there's both a who and a what.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:07:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the what is the momentary expression of that who.\NWho is being whatever that person is being at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.26,0:07:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIt's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.02,0:07:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\NIt's okay to be both who and what.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.48,0:07:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIn fact, you really have to be both a who and a what at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.22,0:07:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because who is it that's being a what?\NWell, do you think that the ego comes in to play when the who is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.73,0:07:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the who, yes.\NThe who is the...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.89,0:07:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Inter...\NIs the villain, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.93,0:07:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The who.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.27,0:07:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And the what is...\NIs the external expression of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.95,0:07:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, everybody is both who and what at the same time, all the time.\NIf you think about who, then you get sort of expanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.94,0:07:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you get embarrassed or nervous.\NI don't know who's speaking right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.54,0:08:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess me, yeah.\NBut what is it that's speaking?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.98,0:08:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because whatever is speaking right now is happening spontaneously.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.74,0:08:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have time to give thought to what I'm going to say.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.00,0:08:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't give me any time to say or to think about it.\NWhat's it all about, baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.99,0:08:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Is real success how people see you or how you see yourself?\NWell, real success, I think, fulfills both.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.23,0:08:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be really successful and keep it privately to yourself.\NThat's real success.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.19,0:08:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You fulfill your own goals.\NYou don't need public rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.27,0:08:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need recognition.\NIf my goal is to chop down this tree and have it all sawed up by 4 o'clock this afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.37,0:08:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,then when I do that, I'm a real success.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.91,0:09:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And nobody knows about it except myself.\NSo, real success to me is then the self-fulfillment of a self-goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.68,0:09:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And the world may or may not even notice it.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.84,0:09:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I have to make myself happy.\NSo, we're talking...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm talking this morning, and I have to make myself happy that I'm understanding the points that you are trying to stimulate me to focus on.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.15,0:09:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I'm not sure what you're wanting me to focus on, then I'm not happy.\NAm I applying myself to what you want me to focus on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.62,0:09:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThen I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.84,0:09:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sweetheart.\NOh, gee, that was an easy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.08,0:09:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are hard to hire.\NYou're an easy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.62,0:10:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When we become judgmental, do we judge people for who they are, or do we judge people for what they are?\NWell, we do both.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.19,0:10:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We do both.\NThe mind really doesn't choose either or.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.83,0:10:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It spontaneously does them all at the same time.\NThe person is famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.25,0:10:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They should be famous.\NWe're glad they're famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We're glad they're famous.\NWe're glad they're famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.55,0:10:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes we criticize somebody because they're famous for what we consider to be the wrong reasons.\NThey've committed a crime or done something hideous, and so we're critical of them for being famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.82,0:10:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They're really not famous.\NThey're really infamous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.60,0:10:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Infamous.\NSo, when fame reaches the height of negativity, we call it infamous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.72,0:11:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Infamous rather than famous.\NPeople, you know, serial killers and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.66,0:11:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't say they're famous.\NWe say they're infamous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.72,0:11:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that people sometimes set goals for themselves a little high?\NLike, you know, sometimes people have higher expectations than they're willing to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.68,0:11:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NWell, I think you can set the goal as high as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.77,0:11:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And the expectations...\NExpectation has to be then tailored to what's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.52,0:11:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can set your goal to be President of the United States,\Nbut only one person is going to achieve that every four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.24,0:11:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's nothing wrong with setting it as a goal and hoping to be the best.\NI hope that we speak in a clearly eloquent and hopeful style this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.52,0:11:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a hope.\NAnd I would like to...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.36,0:12:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that we've achieved that goal, that we've been able to help clarify\Nthat's an important part of human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.78,0:12:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we don't like to admit that it's a big part, but frankly, it is.\NFrankly, it's a big part, whether you have friends that like you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.78,0:12:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're well thought of in your neighborhood\Nand you're successful at whatever your work is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.36,0:12:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Those things are important.\NYou'd like to pretend they're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.54,0:12:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if it's shoveling the sidewalk,\Nwhen you get through shoveling all the snow off the sidewalk,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.46,0:12:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you stand back and you look at it, you feel pleased.\NSo, I guess just feeling pleased and satisfied is sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.97,0:12:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just shovel all the snow off, nobody slipped and hurt themselves,\Nand you feel good that you've fulfilled your responsibility as a good neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.30,0:13:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, true success is on different levels, then, actually.\NSo, you have your personal success, such as chopping the tree up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.89,0:13:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and getting it done by 4 o'clock.\NYou have your financial success, which is the goals you set for yourself outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.97,0:13:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You have your spiritual success, which is your relationship with God.\NAnd then you have, you know, family and everything else that are other successes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.37,0:13:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know...\NRelationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.65,0:13:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Relationship.\NA good wife, a good husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.75,0:13:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, actually, success, when we lump it together, that's unfair\Nbecause there's so many different types of success.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.81,0:13:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, personal success, marital success, parental success.\NWhen your kid gets a good mark at school and comes home with a thing on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.46,0:13:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when I was a kid, if you got good marks, you got a little star on your collar.\NSo, I couldn't wait to get home and show my mom my star on my collar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.66,0:14:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, what have you got there?\NI said, star, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.82,0:14:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, oh, boy.\NDidn't you tell me about a teacher you once had that you were telling...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.56,0:14:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You were very intellectual anyway, but you came home and told a story about something.\NI forgot what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.52,0:14:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A steamship or something like that.\NAnd the teacher told your parents you had a very imaginative imagination, and here it was all true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.08,0:14:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born with a genius.\NAnd so I was often smarter than the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.50,0:14:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the teacher would give a short lecture on something,\Nand then I would correct the teacher because I didn't understand the subtleties of such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:15:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the teacher would explain their understanding, but I, as I said, had a genius IQ.\NAnd I knew the whole encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.71,0:15:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I would elaborate on it for the teacher's benefit and the class's benefit.\NI didn't do it for my benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.15,0:15:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought they'd like to know the facts, which I had read the encyclopedia already about.\NWhen I was a kid, I read the encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.02,0:15:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Other kids are reading the funny papers.\NIt seems very funny now that I was reading the encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.13,0:15:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I got up to R, and I thought, oh, whammo, I'm up to R already, you know what I mean?\NI've only been at it a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.34,0:15:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A week?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.88,0:15:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It took you a week to read things?\NTo get up to R, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.22,0:15:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my gosh.\NWell, that would be a success in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.66,0:15:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I finished X, Y, and Z in the meantime.\NZebra, Zappo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.72,0:16:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But, I mean, those are successes in their own right.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.38,0:16:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, I was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.90,0:16:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's successes to fulfill your own goal.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.84,0:16:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I was one time digging a ditch, and I set myself as a goal to dig six feet a day.\NWell, six feet a ditch depends on how deep it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.77,0:16:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be quite a chore.\NIt can be shallow, it's not much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.95,0:16:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it's deep, six feet a day is a lot of digging.\NAnd I can remember when I dug six feet a day of ditch, and I said, wow, that was a great day, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.53,0:16:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAll stone and rock, and six feet of it was quite an accomplishment, especially when you were a small ectomorph like I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.29,0:16:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you were to...\NI was an ectomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.73,0:16:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou know what an ectomorph is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.83,0:16:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOkay, well, I was a small ectomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.26,0:17:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I started digging a six-foot ditch was quite an accomplishment.\NSo, if you were to tell people what type of goals they should set for themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.12,0:17:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as it goes, as spiritual goals, what would you say?\NYou're going to divide them up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.36,0:17:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I was going to divide them up myself.\NOh, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.82,0:17:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say, all right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'll do it your way.\NNo, that's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.22,0:17:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual goals, you know, would be different for every person, I think.\NSome people would only consider becoming enlightened itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.87,0:17:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the fulfillment.\NOther people, they just believe in God in the first place, or to even go to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.42,0:17:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I know people who never even go to church.\NAnd finally on, what do you want to call it, day?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ash Wednesday.\NAsh Wednesday, they went to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.41,0:18:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that was an achievement for them, to just go to church and to fulfill the goal of,\Nat least the external appearances of...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.84,0:18:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion, religiosity.\NWe went to church on...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.27,0:18:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ash Wednesday.\NAsh Wednesday, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.57,0:18:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the name itself seemed mysterious, you know.\NAsh, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.80,0:18:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashes to ashes and dust to dust.\NOh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.08,0:18:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, you can contemplate on that for a couple of years.\NAshes to ashes and dust to dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.56,0:18:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that fully signify?\NWell, the intellect has a quick answer for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.09,0:19:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you begin to contemplate, ashes to ashes and dust to dust,\NI look at you and I say, you and I are both going to become ashes someday, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.04,0:19:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, honey, you never saw a U-Haul following a hearse, have you?\NOh, that's a funny one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.46,0:19:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Very funny one.\NSo we can't take it with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.50,0:19:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't take it with you, no.\NWell, you don't want to take it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.69,0:19:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be excess baggage in heaven, yes.\NAnd heaven is more of a state of being rather than a state of doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NPeople say, what do you do in heaven?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.90,0:20:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's nothing to do except just be.\NSo just being is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.67,0:20:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To do.\NWe went to church for some really Sunday there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.87,0:20:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And it wasn't, it had nothing to do with what was being done.\NIt was all the who of and the significance of the presence and the symbolism of it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.70,0:20:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The symbolism of reverence for the presence of God as existence is,\Nis,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.88,0:20:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is,\Ndone at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.96,0:20:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the hands are doing it of themselves.\NAnd I look at the hands and I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,hands, what are you expressing?\NYou're not expressing what I'm thinking because I'm not thinking anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.12,0:21:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask the hands to express the reverence of the presence of,\Nthe awareness of the presence of God as existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.15,0:21:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thank the hands for fulfilling that obligation.\NSo with the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.44,0:21:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,uh,\Nit thinks the mind can then represent and therefore with a certain level of intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.24,0:21:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,every moment is expressing the presence of God.\NThe divinity of the presence of God is expressing itself every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.99,0:21:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,\Nit cannot be otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.09,0:21:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only be the failure,\Nthe ability to recognize it as such or the inability to recognize it as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.76,0:21:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you and I sit here and speak,\NI say,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.00,0:22:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel by using whatever talents I may have in the service of,\Nof the Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.26,0:22:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm serving God by sitting here next to you and you're doing the same thing\Nwith me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.58,0:22:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you and I right now are serving God to the best of our knowledge to share our\Nunderstanding of divinity and the intention of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.47,0:22:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and how to fulfill that.\NThat may not be somebody else's,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.06,0:22:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't make any difference\Nbecause I want to hear everybody's idea on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.93,0:22:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to hear everybody's thoughts\Non how do I fulfill God's obligation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.31,0:22:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or my responsibility to God.\NI think that's a really interesting question
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.68,0:22:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to ask everybody.\NI'd like to ask a whole dozen different people
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.59,0:22:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,doing different things in the world.\NHow do you feel you're fulfilling God's obligation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.71,0:23:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and get the interesting answers?\NI go to work every day and I support my children
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.22,0:23:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and I pay my taxes and I'm good to my wife\Nand I shovel the snow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.24,0:23:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I make sure the car has gas in it.\NFulfilling one's obligation to human life
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.50,0:23:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way of fulfilling the intention of divinity\Nbecause it is through divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.91,0:23:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that we experience life.\NAnd at least it's human form.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.82,0:23:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people think that success\Nis actually changing the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.20,0:23:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,making a difference in the world.\NThat's worldly success, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.02,0:23:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah, but a lot of people set their goals at that.\NOh, I see, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.98,0:23:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to change the thought\Nof everyone around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.64,0:23:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NTo make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.66,0:23:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Influence.\NYeah, they want to put their mark
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.70,0:24:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,on the world.\NSo what you're saying is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.70,0:24:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by being a better person spiritually,\Nyou do put your mark on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.12,0:24:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We do it silently.\NBut we do it silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.94,0:24:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThe fact that you're present in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.16,0:24:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,makes what goes on in the room differently.\NLet's see if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.55,0:24:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me have your hand.\NEven if you say nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.54,0:24:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of a...\Nspiritually advanced person in a room
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.22,0:24:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,changes everything that happens in that room.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.42,0:24:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.\NSo even if you just lay on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.14,0:24:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and say nothing,\Nthe energy that you emanate
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.55,0:24:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is affecting everything around you.\NWell, that's a nice thing to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.12,0:24:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're light.\NIn other words, your life has value
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.84,0:24:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time,\Neven though you're not out there
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.76,0:24:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,doing spectacular things,\Nbeing famous, writing famous music,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.22,0:25:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,appearing on stage,\Nor just...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.64,0:25:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's have the arm again.\NJust being the excellence
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.67,0:25:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the possibility within yourself\Nof whatever it may be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.63,0:25:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is serving God.\NOkay, to sing the best song you can sing,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.71,0:25:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to dance the best dance,\Nyou and I right now
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.48,0:25:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,are fulfilling an obligation to each other.\NYou said we're going to be giving
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.72,0:25:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a little talk this morning\Nthat we're going to be recording,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.32,0:25:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was thinking,\NI was panic-stricken.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.90,0:25:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, oh, my God,\NI haven't thought about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.12,0:25:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to talk about?\NAnd as we sat down here,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.14,0:25:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,my inner mind said,\Noh, my God,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.84,0:25:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what are we going to talk about?\NAnd right now, my mind is saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.61,0:25:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, my God,\Nwhat are we going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.75,0:25:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea\Nwhat we're going to be speaking about
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.20,0:25:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning.\NLet me have your arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.26,0:25:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI just wanted you to give me my arm
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.48,0:26:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for no reason this morning.\NI didn't like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.46,0:26:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't like this.\NI think it's important to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.10,0:26:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I already asked you before.\NI thought if it was not God's intention
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.06,0:26:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for me to be sitting here\Nspeaking to you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.28,0:26:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in the style in which I am,\Nthere is no other possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.30,0:26:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,except to be doing\Nwhat God wants me to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.75,0:26:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,which is sitting here\Ncommenting to you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.01,0:26:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,on your presence\Nand the effect that it has on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.89,0:26:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So you, as yourself,\Nwhat would you say
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.14,0:26:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you say success looks like to you?\NTo me?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.23,0:26:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.23,0:26:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you share that with us?\NWell, to me, success means multiple things simultaneously, because you might ask it from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.31,0:27:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,different areas.\NAm I being successful in fulfilling your expectation of me this morning to come forth and spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.06,0:27:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,answer these questions?\NThat's what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.87,0:27:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm happy that I am fulfilling what I understood was your question to me.\NCould we go into the studio and discuss a few of these important questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.15,0:27:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I feel satisfied that I am fulfilling your expectation of me.\NAnd so I'm hoping that my doing so makes you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.20,0:27:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So your happiness is part of my intention all the time.\NI mean, I always want you to be happy, and there's no moment when I ... I've never had
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.08,0:27:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a wish that you should not be happy.\NNever.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.92,0:27:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I never crossed my mind.\NI want you to be happy all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.97,0:28:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the only reason I'm worried about how the doggies are behaving is I want the doggies\Nto add to your happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.99,0:28:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want the doggie to have an accident, which would detract from your happiness.\NSo that's why we let the doggie out, to make sure that the doggie wouldn't interrupt our
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.75,0:28:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillment of this obligation this morning.\NIs the search for enlightenment or bettering one's spiritual understanding, is that ... it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.69,0:28:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,an entirely different success than, say, worldly success?\NWell, yes, spiritually, success has nothing to do with the world, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.65,0:28:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,On one level, it has everything to do with it, but on the level at which you're asking\Nit, it has really nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.15,0:29:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because success is an inner goal, an inner expectation, partly based on an awareness\Nof what your capacities are.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.48,0:29:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I feel I've successfully, adequately answered your questions, then I'll feel satisfied\Nthat I've adequately addressed them, carefully listened to them, and allowed themselves to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.14,0:29:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously answer.\NSo these moments that we have right this very instant are all happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.84,0:29:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea of what they are.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.53,0:29:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to talk about, other than that we were going to be here to speak.\NSo I trust, there's a certain trust, there's a certain inner trust that my inner self will
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.20,0:30:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically adjust itself to fulfill the expectations of the moment, one of them being\Nthat your satisfaction at the way in which I'm answering you right this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.55,0:30:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm feeling happy that you ... you might possibly be happy with the way I'm answering\Nyou right this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.57,0:30:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm feeling happy that you ... you might possibly be happy with the way I'm answering\Nyou right this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.57,0:30:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be happy with the way I'm being right now.\NAre you being happy with the way I'm being right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.51,0:30:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAre you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.51,0:30:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.67,0:30:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not just saying that to make me feel good.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.41,0:30:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's another ... you have to put a point down.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.07,0:30:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So a lot of people that are successful in their spiritual life do not have worldly success.\NI mean, that's ...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.25,0:30:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NYou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.25,0:30:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because ... do you think it's because they concentrated all their ... I mean that the\NSpiritual success is more important to them than worldly?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.72,0:30:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.\NAnd the fulfillment is of spiritual goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.76,0:30:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day we went to church for, what is it,\NHappy Wednesday morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.02,0:31:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call it?\NAsh Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.02,0:31:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NAsh Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.10,0:31:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Ash Wednesday, right.\NUnhappy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.82,0:31:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we got there on time,\Nfulfilled the obligation to ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.14,0:31:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that we decided we wished to do that.\NNot everybody goes, and we didn't always go every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.26,0:31:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Some years you feel like for some reason\Nit's important that we go this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.30,0:31:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be for unknown reasons.\NI think most things happen for unknown reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.05,0:31:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I think our mind gives us an explanation,\Nbut I think the explanation may have very little to do
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.23,0:31:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with the reality.\NThere was possibly people affected just by our physical presence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.31,0:32:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in the room itself, of which we had no comprehension.\NA little doggy barking by the side of the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.68,0:32:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't know he's barking to make you happy,\Nbut that may be what keeps a little sick kid alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.98,0:32:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The puppy that loves the sick child keeps the child alive.\NThe sick puppy doesn't know it's doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.37,0:32:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the puppy doesn't know it's doing it.\NBut there are children in hospitals whose lives are extended
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.58,0:32:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by the presence of having a puppy or a dog.\NAnd I think the study of the effect of dogs on human life
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.22,0:32:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is very, very fascinating.\NNot only that it extends your life ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.61,0:32:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but it increases the quality.\NSo the quality of our life is much higher
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.54,0:32:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,since we got Kelsey dog.\NAnd I don't know what Kelsey cost us, five bucks?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.93,0:32:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.91,0:32:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NThree?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.91,0:32:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NFifteen?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.91,0:32:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We adopted her, so no, it wasn't that.\NNo?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.41,0:33:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NAnyway, the presence of that dog in our life makes a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.30,0:33:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And even now as we speak, in the back of my mind,\NI realize the dog is sitting home waiting for us to come home
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.80,0:33:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from the studio.\NAnd that as we get closer and closer, her tail will start to wag.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.80,0:33:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,She will feel happier and happier and more and more excited.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.80,0:33:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes life joyful.\NThe fact that your existence brings joy to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.99,0:33:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I approach the kitties, they start to purr.\NThe big orange kitty always goes purr, purr, purr, purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.31,0:33:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And that makes me happy.\NI can hear the kitties' happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.31,0:33:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the doggie's tail is wagging.\NAnd then we've got an African talking parrot.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.31,0:33:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that his name? African talking parrot?\NAfrican gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.31,0:33:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,African gray.\NAnd the parrot starts talking up a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.31,0:33:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So the kitty's purring.\NThe dog's tail is wagging.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.31,0:34:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the African gray parrot is talking up a big storm there.\NIt's called a zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.31,0:34:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All of that adds to the joy of life.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.31,0:34:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NA joie de vivre.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.53,0:34:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I like that word, joie de vivre.\NJoie de vivre.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.53,0:34:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Joie, joie de vivre.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.53,0:34:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you would say is, I mean, it's kind of common knowledge that a spiritual aspirant a lot of times is not as successful in the world as other people because that just seems to be secondary to them.\NYeah, that's pretty true.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.56,0:34:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A secondary goal.\NIt's okay to have money, but it's considered a detriment.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.56,0:34:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYeah, many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.56,0:34:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NEnough to have, you know, your needs fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.78,0:34:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, that's all you really need.\NAnd the rest is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.94,0:35:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NI've got a new pair of shoes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.71,0:35:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm proud of them.\NWhenever I see my...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.71,0:35:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see new shoes?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.71,0:35:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, those are new shoes.\NI'm very proud of these new shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.71,0:35:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I haven't had a new pair of shoes in, I don't know, years.\NSo, to me, a new pair of shoes is a big, exciting event.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.71,0:35:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.71,0:35:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I have to break them in.\NI've decided that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.71,0:35:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The upside is you have a new pair of shoes.\NThe downside is you have to break it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.71,0:35:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, I think everybody should enjoy these brand new shoes, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.71,0:35:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But it couldn't get simpler, really.\NSo, success is a name that we put on an act that, whether it's a new business or a new
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.71,0:35:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,business, it's a new business.\NIt's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.71,0:35:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.\NIt's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.71,0:35:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.\NIt's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.71,0:35:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.\NIt's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.48,0:35:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I mean, we're, it's, and actually, the more important success is the personal success\Nrather than the worldly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.95,0:35:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI mean, to certain people that would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.81,0:36:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, other people, worldly success is what they would.\NIt is worldly, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.57,0:36:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't divide the two.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.57,0:36:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to some people, they want the same thing.\NTo achieve worldly success.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.76,0:36:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for instance, what I'm trying to do right now is answer your question.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.76,0:36:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,questions to the best of my capability.\NWhat the world thinks of it is rather irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.26,0:36:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, wasn't it Carnegie, who's a big steel manufacturer, and he was very successful\Nand had all this money, and he gave all of it away at the end of his life?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.10,0:36:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that he had accomplished his whole life, he gave away.\NWell, I think that's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.86,0:36:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What else are you going to do with it?\NYou can't take it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.94,0:36:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what he did is he created these museums and...\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.18,0:36:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I see what you're saying, yes.\NSo that other people could enjoy...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.70,0:36:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NI think that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.70,0:36:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.70,0:37:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was Carnegie.\NWhat you're trying to do is share your success with the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.59,0:37:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that we have people who are interested in listening to us speak with each other,\Nthe fact that that is so makes our life successful, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.98,0:37:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIsn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.78,0:37:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NBut I mean, I know wealthy people, and that would be the last thing they would do, is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.17,0:37:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to give everything, their whole life, you know, they wouldn't want to give it all away.\NWell, you can't take it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.59,0:37:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you do with it?\NI know, but I mean, there's lots of people that pass it along or whatever, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.61,0:37:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next generation.\NOh, oh, I see what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.59,0:37:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NControl of their wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.59,0:37:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NControl of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.59,0:37:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NControl of it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.59,0:37:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NAll right, that's just, you know, people don't have to be ashamed of normal human emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.74,0:38:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Normal human emotions is to crave success, recognition, worldly goods, comfort.\NThose are just normal for the human.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.27,0:38:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think a person should feel guilty about it.\NI mean, I hope people enjoy our discussion right now, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.36,0:38:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that selfish, or is it just the goodwill, or it's just the fact that I care about people\Nand their happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.25,0:38:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them to enjoy the moment, and that what we're speaking about with each other\Nstimulates a similar positive response within them, so I'm not just talking to you so that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.41,0:38:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we can play this back and enjoy ourselves talking to each other, because I've already\Nheard what we had to say, you know, but what you want to do is share your enjoyment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.94,0:38:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same as if you play piano or something.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.48,0:39:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there was a great pianist, pretty well-known pianist, and in fact, we had two, we owned\Ntwo pianos in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.87,0:39:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody in the house played piano, and everybody played it to the best of their ability, so\Nwe enjoyed each other's capacity and capabilities as a pianist, and then I took up the violin
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.42,0:39:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,instead.\NPlus, I was also a singer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.77,0:39:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI was also a well-known boy soprano, and so I had this incredible singing voice, plus
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.78,0:39:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I could play the violin, plus I could play the piano, so, and then I enjoyed music, and\NI still do listen to a great orchestra, so the enjoyment of music and all of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.52,0:39:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,adds to the joy of life.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.24,0:39:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, on the way home, if we had to go home, we'd go home.\NIf we had a little music in the electric cart that we're going to go home in, I'd probably
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.36,0:40:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,play the music to add to the celebration of this morning.\NWouldn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.19,0:40:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.20,0:40:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So—\NI just got the name of that song.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.58,0:40:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Merrily, we rolled along.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.60,0:40:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I like it.\Nso it's it's a choice that we have to make whether we want a spirit whether we
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.72,0:40:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,consider spiritual success more important to us or we consider financial\Nsuccess yeah yeah whether we're going to divide them up that way and classify
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.50,0:40:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,them is that way right because you can be financially successful and also\Nspiritually right they don't preclude each other right and you can be rich as
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.46,0:41:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,all get out and not pious or you can be very pious and very poor it's better to\Nbe rich and pious it's better to go home from church in a Cadillac than peddling
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.15,0:41:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself in a rusty old bicycle a modicum of it so all these things come\Ndown to balance right you know religiosity you can also become a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.50,0:41:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,religious nut you know\Nreligious nut you know
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.14,0:41:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,religious nut you know\Npain in the neck so all these things is a matter of balance how much time you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.29,0:41:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and I spend with each other talking and laughing with each other how much time\Nwe spend with our doggy and playing with her dog so it seems to me that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.17,0:42:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,everything we do is a matter of balance there's a bad matter of balance of\Naffection of playfulness of rest of sleep of work of wash their
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.01,0:42:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the car when it needs being washed so life is a is a constant uh fluctuating diversity\Nover which we have no control whether it rains today or it doesn't so if if one could
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.81,0:42:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,balance their life between their spiritual goals and their successful goals then you could have\Nboth you can certainly have both and certainly being spiritual is part of my idea is successful
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.55,0:42:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh other people might consider it only you know financial successes at this so it would be\Nthe self-fulfillment of our own comprehension and understanding which is our level of maturity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.40,0:43:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course how old you are uh-huh and you mean at 92 you're going to be more interested\Nin whether heaven's a reality or not than at 18 right
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.18,0:43:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you\Ni guess yeah you're right so as well i think it's the hindus that that um they they you know
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.72,0:43:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,give up everything at the end of their life and and devote everything to god or i don't know it's\Njust restricted anybody i i thought everybody did that sort of well yes i mean material things get
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.20,0:43:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,rid of things well i don't know if it's material but they what they do do is they do do a lot of\Nit's they devote the last part of their life to god oh okay yeah so if we all would take those
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.94,0:43:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,lessons and devote um you know the first part of your life it's you know you're young and then you\Nhave babies and then you have you know then you go into the to the later part of your life and as
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.16,0:44:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you reach the later part of your life you realize that you're you're spiritual um because it becomes\Nmore important oh yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.56,0:44:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so it would be nice if we could balance that throughout our life rather than just\Nexpecting that to happen at the end yes well i think people are brought up properly uh that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.26,0:44:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that does happen okay you know as a kid you go to sunday school and uh while your folks are in\Nchurch you're at sunday school and then as you get older then finally you get married when you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.97,0:44:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,do that you do that with the priest and the church\Nand uh it doesn't mean that it's wrong to be non-spiritual or not materialistic i mean to be
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.64,0:45:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,materialistic it's not wrong uh that people are not spiritually interested i feel that's just not\Nan area of their life that karmically is important at this moment it might be in fact quite the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.47,0:45:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite you know quit up put all that praying and get the car washed\Nokay
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.24,0:45:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,let's have let's praying a little more work around here\Nif you prayed all day instead of cook that have complaints before you know what all right
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.76,0:45:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,don't we ever eat around this joint everybody not yet i come on you think\Nwe're just busy praying
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.42,0:45:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,i'll have to try that\Ni'm gonna try that see how that works
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.64,0:45:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,when you tell me today we're gonna pray a little more work around here\Nhaving meatloaf. Isn't that right? Okay, so yeah that'd be something I'd sit down at
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.15,0:46:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,dinner and she says, I didn't get the dinner done. And I'd say, why do you? Because I was\Npraying we didn't get the meatloaf cooked. Then I'd feel guilty, see, that I'm mad
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.66,0:46:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that you, you know, that I want my meatloaf instead of having you pray. So\Nthat would make me feel materialistic and greedy, that I'm concerned about my
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.33,0:46:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,eating instead of her praying. I should be concerned about whether she prays\Nnot whether I eat meatloaf or not. You know, it's funny how human feeling can be so
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.23,0:46:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,intricate and circuitous in many ways, seemingly ambivalent, ambiguous, rather.\NSo would you say that success is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.41,0:46:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a\Njust a term that we put on a act or a, how do I want to say, I'm trying to think how to say this,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.25,0:47:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,success is a word that we put to an action. Or an achievement. Or achievement. Or a state of being.\NOr a state of being. Worldly or spiritual or intellectual, it could apply to any.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.58,0:47:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectually you get straight A in school, you did well. Mm-hmm.\NGo to church with sincerity in your heart. That would be a fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.91,0:47:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But you brought up the fact that balance is very important between all of them.\NYes, I think extremes otherwise make your prayer sort of quirky.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.91,0:47:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to pray all day but somebody's got to shovel the sidewalk, you know what I'm saying?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.07,0:47:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.\NSo.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.69,0:47:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI think that's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.17,0:47:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.59,0:47:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good question.\NWell, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.49,0:47:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's a good question.\NI think that's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.22,0:47:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.48,0:47:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's a good question.\NWell, that's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.74,0:47:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.98,0:47:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.22,0:47:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.30,0:47:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.44,0:47:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.54,0:47:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\Nas as a teacher would you call yourself successful? Oh successful well I'm happy
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.28,0:48:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm successful and then I'm happy that I have a chance to speak spontaneously in\Na forthright and honest way that is not stilted and stylized which which often
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.86,0:48:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,turns people off on what they consider spiritual but many people are turned off\Nby anything they hear is spiritual because they expect all this holy roller
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.28,0:48:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,stylized not too realistic kind of expression of prayerfulness and\Nholiness and you know you might say excess being spontaneously joyful and
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.32,0:48:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,being spontaneously the reality of that which I am I consider that spiritual\Ngive me a kiss
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.95,0:49:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think of that it just was I wanted to like say thank you God that you\Nbrought the thought to my mind which I meant to express and I'm very happy to
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.53,0:49:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to do that I mean I'm only have this body for a while and I want to use\Nit to express my understanding of spirituality because it might be a value
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.89,0:49:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to someone else\Nsomebody served it's value to me but it might be helpful to somebody else so as
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.57,0:49:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a more stilted view of it so my view of spirituality is probably less stilted\Nthan some people who tend to be sanctimonious you know you might say
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.95,0:49:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,sanctimonious and think that being spiritual is an awkward and difficult\Nway of life sackcloth and ashes kind of deal mm-hmm not there's any wrong with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.58,0:50:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But as a spiritual teacher you know we've as us we've tried to convey every question\Nthat maybe the spiritual person would ask so that's why we're doing these talks
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.96,0:50:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think yes we're trying and we're trying to record it and so that if questions arise\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.06,0:50:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,they will be answered\Nso we're trying to expand
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.62,0:50:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the understanding\Nof what's meant by the term
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.66,0:50:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual\Nor success
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.40,0:50:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of people really dwell on success\NI'm not successful unless
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.96,0:50:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a million dollars\Nin the bank
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.26,0:50:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or I'm not successful unless I get that job\Nor I'm not successful unless I have that car
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.64,0:50:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so they have their own definitions\Nand those are all goals
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.70,0:51:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that people set for each other\Nbut you brought up the fact that they need to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.60,0:51:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,balance that\Nbetween their spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.52,0:51:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,life and\Nthe monetary
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.26,0:51:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,success of life\Nthey will be more successful if they balance it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.12,0:51:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,than if they just\Nfocus on success itself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.92,0:51:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because just\Nworldly success
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.34,0:51:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as a 100% focus\Ntends to turn people off
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.42,0:51:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to a certain extent\Nyou watch them on television
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.84,0:51:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell\Nyou can tell
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.48,0:51:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell\Nthey're all about me, me, me, me, me
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.10,0:51:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and that tends to turn you off after a while\Nand that's one
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.92,0:51:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reason we like comedians\Nis because comedians tend to make light of their
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.24,0:51:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human limitations\Nto make humorous
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.70,0:51:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what would otherwise be painful\Nserves a spiritual purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.70,0:51:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I also thought humorous\Ntended for a long life
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.70,0:52:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and the contribution of humor\Nto life
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.25,0:52:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because they help us to laugh at ourself\Nat what otherwise
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.79,0:52:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,might be quite painful\Nand embarrassing
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.96,0:52:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we can take ourselves\NJack Benny can take us
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.46,0:52:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we can take ourselves lightly\NI guess that dates me
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.84,0:52:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack Benny is he\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.04,0:52:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,yes\Nis he still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.92,0:52:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,no\Noh no
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.38,0:52:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway Jack Benny\Nsymbolizes the ultimate of the
